    "This explains the p = q = r = 1 piece of statement 1.5.This fact is usually presented by saying that L 1 cannot be screened to another line operator L 2, if L 1 and L 2 have different charges under the 1-form symmetry.",
    "In particular, a line operator L carrying a non-trivial charge under 1-form symmetry cannot be completely screened, i.e.",
    "cannot be screened to the identity line operator.",
    "Twisted generalized chargesIn this section we study higher-charges formed by operators living in twisted sectors of invertible symmetries.",
    "These, as defined in section 1.4, arise at the end of symmetry generators or condensation defects."
